  <!-- Introduction Section -->
  <section class="py-20 bg-background">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
        <h2 class="text-3xl sm:text-4xl font-display font-bold text-text mb-6">
          What Is Built-in CRM Software?
        </h2>
        <div
          class="prose prose-lg max-w-none text-text-muted leading-relaxed space-y-6"
        >
          <p>
            Built-in CRM software combines customer relationship management
            functionality directly within your scheduling platform, eliminating
            the need for separate tools. Unlike traditional CRM systems that
            require integration with external calendar tools, CalendHub's
            built-in CRM provides contact management, deal pipeline tracking,
            service organization, and customer interaction history all in one
            unified interface. This all-in-one scheduling CRM approach means you
            can manage customer relationships and schedule appointments without
            ever switching between applications.
          </p>
          <p>
            CalendHub's unique approach to built-in CRM centers customer data
            around your scheduling activities. When a client books a meeting,
            their information automatically flows into your contact database.
            When you complete a consultation, you can immediately log notes,
            update deal stages, and schedule follow-ups without opening a
            separate CRM tool. This scheduling software with CRM built-in
            creates a seamless workflow where customer tracking happens
            naturally as part of your daily scheduling routine, not as a
            separate administrative task.
          </p>
          <p>
            Traditional standalone CRM platforms like HubSpot and Salesforce
            were designed for large sales teams and require substantial setup,
            ongoing maintenance, and separate calendar integrations. Many
            professionals—coaches, consultants, service providers, and small
            business owners—find these enterprise CRM solutions overly complex
            for their needs. They end up paying for features they don't use
            while still needing to maintain separate scheduling tools.
            CalendHub's built-in CRM eliminates this complexity by focusing on
            what scheduling-centric businesses actually need: simple contact
            management, service tracking, deal pipelines, and customer
            interaction history, all integrated with appointment scheduling.
          </p>
          <p>
            Beyond eliminating tool switching, CalendHub's built-in CRM
            prioritizes data privacy and reliability. Your customer information
            stays within a single secure platform rather than being synchronized
            across multiple systems where data can become outdated or
            inconsistent. Automated workflows trigger based on booking behavior,
            deal stages update based on completed meetings, and customer
            timelines automatically populate with each interaction. This creates
            a living database that maintains itself through your normal
            scheduling activities, giving you the benefits of sophisticated
            customer tracking without the administrative overhead of traditional
            CRM systems.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- How It Works Section -->
  <section class="py-32 relative overflow-hidden">
    <div class="container relative z-10">
